 \\\"may have alienated too many new viewers to garner the anticipated response from our Olympic premiere,\\\" said Zack Slusser, vice president of Breaking for Gold USA and USA Dance, in a text message to the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3718, \"end\": 3722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\", \"score\": 0.9999999993474376, \"rank\": 6.509808699504159e-10, \"text\": \"Zack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\"}, {\"begin\": 3812, \"end\": 3828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9984889883555449, \"rank\": 0.001513298255523355, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Friday night's slips\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"too many new viewers\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3649}, {\"ngram\": \"the anticipated response\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3684}, {\"ngram\": \"our Olympic premiere\", \"from\": 3690, \"to\": 3710}, {\"ngram\": \"vice president\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3746}, {\"ngram\": \"Breaking\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3758}, {\"ngram\": \"Gold USA\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3771}, {\"ngram\": \"USA Dance\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3785}, {\"ngram\": \"a text message\", \"from\": 3790, \"to\": 3804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to change the narrative from yesterday's first impression of breaking as an Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the narrative\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3863}, {\"ngram\": \"yesterday's first impression\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3897}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3909}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic sport\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 3929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were significant organizational and governance shortcomings that could have been easily reconciled but, unfortunately, negatively impacted Breaking's first touching point to a new global audience.\\\"\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 4134, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"significant organizational and governance shortcomings\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 3996}, {\"ngram\": \"Breaking's first touching point\", \"from\": 4076, \"to\": 4107}, {\"ngram\": \"a new global audience\", \"from\": 4111, \"to\": 4132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenge for Olympic organizers was to bring breaking and hip-hop culture to a mass audience, including many viewers who were skeptical about the dance form's addition to the Olympic roster.\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4331, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The challenge\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4149}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4172}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking and hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4214}, {\"ngram\": \"a mass audience\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4233}, {\"ngram\": \"many viewers\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4257}, {\"ngram\": \"the dance form's addition\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4308}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic roster\", \"from\": 4312, \"to\": 4330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others feared the subculture being co-opted by officials, commercialized and put through a rigid judging structure when the spirit of breaking has been rooted in local communities, centered around street battles, cyphers and block parties.\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4571, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Others\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4338}, {\"ngram\": \"the subculture\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4360}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 4379, \"to\": 4388}, {\"ngram\": \"a rigid judging structure\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4446}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4462}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4474}, {\"ngram\": \"local communities\", \"from\": 4494, \"to\": 4511}, {\"ngram\": \"street battles\", \"from\": 4529, \"to\": 4543}, {\"ngram\": \"cyphers\", \"from\": 4545, \"to\": 4552}, {\"ngram\": \"block parties\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hip-hop was born as a youth culture within Black and brown communities in the Bronx as a way to escape strife and socio-economic struggles and make a statement of empowerment at a time when they were labeled as lost, lawless kids by New York politicians.\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4650, \"end\": 4655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9224223337644754e-14, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 4805, \"end\": 4813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.90566620467783e-12, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hip-hop\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4579}, {\"ngram\": \"a youth culture\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4607}, {\"ngram\": \"Black and brown communities\", \"from\": 4615, \"to\": 4642}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 4659, \"to\": 4664}, {\"ngram\": \"strife\", \"from\": 4675, \"to\": 4681}, {\"ngram\": \"socio-economic struggles\", \"from\": 4686, \"to\": 4710}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4731}, {\"ngram\": \"empowerment\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4746}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 4750, \"to\": 4756}, {\"ngram\": \"lost, lawless kids\", \"from\": 4783, \"to\": 4801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Refugee breaker Manizha Talash, or \\\"b-girl Talash,\\\" channeled that rebellious